Week 9 

File Handling
-------------

In Java - opening, create , read, write, add, update, delete, close 


files - java project (not related)

File Class - java.io // input & output 

 (Create, delete, read)

canRead(), canWrite(), delete(), exists(), createNewFile(), getName(), getAbsolutePath() //"C:/newfolder/project", length() //bytes, list()//String[], mkdir() //creates directory 

I/O Streams in JAVA : 

Byte Stream - InputStream class (FileInputStream, ByteArrayInputStream, BufferedInputStream) 
              OutputStream class(FileOutputStream, ByteArrayOutputStream, BufferedOutputStream)


Character Stream - Reader(FileReader, BufferReader, )
                   Writer(FileWriter, BufferWriter, )
 

File file = new File("sample.txt"); //File Object  Not a actual physical file

file1, file2

file.createNewFile(); //to create only in in the project dir

file.createNewFile("path/file.txt");  // to specify path

file.getParentFile().mkdirs();


